protected class PrioritizedMap.FIFOIterator
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<E>

An iterator that allows the programmer to traverse the prioritized map. A FIFOIterator starts at level 0 (the highest priority) and returns a new object of this level each time next is called. When the iterator reaches the end of the level, it starts the next level.
